The Bank of Ceylon has introduced a revised Human Resource Policy on Remote Work, which aims to ensure that employees can work efficiently and effectively from remote locations. The policy is applicable to all eligible employees and outlines guidelines and procedures for remote work arrangements. Employees are required to adhere to the policy's terms and conditions, which include standards for remote work locations, equipment, tools, software, and confidentiality.
Key Points:
- All employees of the Bank must adhere to the Human Resource Policy on Remote Work with regard to their official duties and responsibilities.
- A Remote Worker is defined as an Employee who works from any location other than his/her normal designated location at any given time.
- The purpose of the HR Policy on Remote Work is to outline how the Bank will handle employees working remotely, either from home or other locations outside the office.
- Remote Workers must enter into a Remote Work Agreement (RWA) with the Bank prior to commencing remote work.
- The Management reserves the sole discretion to approve or refuse an application for Remote Work Facility.
- Remote Workers are required to report to work on the allocated shift starting time or the working time as agreed under the terms of the Remote Work Agreement.
- Remote Workers must be bound by all policies, procedures, rules and regulations of the Bank at all times, unless specifically exempted in writing.
- The Management will accept no responsibility for damage or repairs to Remote worker-owned equipment.
- Remote Workers are required to clock in and clock out remotely through a prescribed method recommended or created by the Management from time to time to mark their attendance when working remotely.
- Failure to enter attendance will be considered as unauthorized absence except in a situation where the Remote Worker is on approved leave.
- The Bank's liability shall be limited to injuries occurred in the course of or arising out of remote work carried out within the working hours at the Remote Work Location.
- Remote Workers must ensure that all equipment/tools/software supplied for Remote Working by the Management are exclusively used by the Remote Worker and for Remote Work purposes only.
- Remote Workers must report any work-related injury to their supervisor and the Head of the Department immediately.
- The employee must inform his/her immediate family of the requirements of the Remote Work Policy to avoid any interruption while working from home.
- The employee shall be entitled to commence Remote Work upon obtaining approval for the Remote Workstation by the Remote Work Administrator.
- The standards to be maintained by the 'Approved Remote Work Location' shall be as follows:
	+ Workspace Safety: Workspace is clean and orderly, and in an environment that allows for optimal productivity; Workspace is supplied with necessary workstation equipment, and related materials; Workspace is free from indoor air quality problems and has adequate ventilation; Working environment is designed to minimize hazards, and set-up with safety in mind; Workspace is located in a quiet and distraction-free environment.
	+ Electrical: Sufficient electrical outlets are accessible; All outlets are covered and in working order (Caution: Do not overload outlets; make sure they can handle the load; if necessary, call your electrician to verify outlet electrical circuit capacity); Equipment is fitted with grounding adapters, surge protectors, and overload fuses; All grounding adapters and power strips/surge protectors that are being used are functional; Equipment is placed close to electrical outlets; Electrical cords/wires are placed so that there are no tripping hazards; Electrical cords exhibit no evidence of fraying.
	+ Fire Safety: There is a working smoke detector in the workspace and batteries or power supply will be checked regularly; A home multi-purpose, fully charged fire extinguisher, which you know how to use, is readily available; You have an evacuation plan so you know what to do in the event of a fire; Exits allow for prompt evacuation.
	+ Workspace Illumination: Lighting is optimal for user, taking natural light into account; If lighting and/or window placement creates problems, the Remote Worker is responsible for adjusting work station as needed; A clear photograph of the workspace illumination is attached.
- The employee shall be bound by Bank's Code of Conduct, Policies, Procedure, Rules and Regulations. It is the responsibility of the employee to be updated of all such Policies, Procedures etc. If in doubt of any provisions applicable to the employee, the employee shall contact …………… for clarifications.
- The Management will accept no responsibility for damage or repairs to Remote worker-owned equipment.
- Remote Workers are required to use authorized methods of communication as detailed in the Remote

