----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T16:48:41.572310 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 01/2021: SUSPENSION OF RECOVERY ACTIONS AGAINST SMALL AND MEDIUM ENTERPRISE (SME) PADDY MILLERS

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
Licensed commercial banks and licensed specialised banks are required to suspend recovery actions against Small and Medium Enterprise (SME) Paddy Millers for a period of six months due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This suspension is aimed at supporting SME Paddy Millers amidst the Government's initiatives. The suspension applies from January 1, 2021.

Key Points:
- Licensed banks must suspend recovery actions against SME Paddy Millers until June 30, 2021.
- Recovery actions can be suspended on condition that a debt re-payment agreement is reached between the bank and the borrower.
- In cases where resolutions for recovery have already been passed, auctioning of assets will be suspended until June 30, 2021.
- Licensed banks must defer passing new resolutions under relevant Acts until June 30, 2021.
- Borrowers with on-going litigations in courts relating to recovery can enter into an agreement by submitting an affidavit to the Courts.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

