----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T16:52:16.176048 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 02/2021: Amendments to Circular No. 04 of 2018 on Guidelines to Licensed Banks on the Adoption of Sri Lanka Accounting Standard – SLFRS 9: Financial Instruments

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
The Central Bank of Sri Lanka has issued an amendment to Circular No. 04 of 2018 regarding the adoption of Sri Lanka Accounting Standard — SLFRS 9: Financial Instruments by licensed banks. This circular aims to establish consistent practices in the adoption of this standard during exceptional circumstances.

Key Points:
- Licensed banks must apply a minimum Loan Loss Coverage (LGD) of 10 per cent when computing expected losses for the year 2021.
- The amendment inserts Guideline 2.5(c) into Circular No. 04 of 2018, which permits this exception.
- This change applies to all licensed banks in Sri Lanka.
- The amendment is effective immediately and supersedes previous guidelines.
- Banks must update their accounting practices accordingly.
- Compliance with the amended guideline is mandatory for all licensed banks.
- The Central Bank will monitor compliance with the new guideline.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

