----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T19:01:58.642799 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 02/2025: Reporting of Information Technology and Cybersecurity Incidents of Licensed Banks

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
Licensed banks in Sri Lanka are required to report IT and cybersecurity incidents to the Central Bank of Sri Lanka (CBSL) to ensure operational resilience and safeguard customer information and assets.

Key Points:
- Licensed banks must report IT and cybersecurity incidents, including intrusion/hacking, malware, ransomware, phishing, and online scams, within 2 hours of detection to the Director, Bank Supervision Department via techrisk.bsd@cbsl.lk.
- Quarterly reports on IT and cybersecurity incidents must be submitted by licensed banks within 15 days following the end of each quarter to the Director, Bank Supervision Department via techrisk.bsd@cbsl.lk.
- Licensed banks are required to submit detailed reports on IT and cybersecurity incidents within 14 working days of detection to the Director, Bank Supervision Department via techrisk.bsd@cbsl.lk.
- The report must include information on the incident, business impact, data and information security impact, stakeholders' and customers' impact, reputational impact, regulatory or legal impact, financial impact, corrective actions taken, and target dates for corrective actions.
- Licensed banks are required to submit a preliminary impact assessment in summary within 2 hours of detection to the Director, Bank Supervision Department via techrisk.bsd@cbsl.lk.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

