----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T19:02:28.208113 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 03/2024: GUIDELINES FOR THE ESTABLISHMENT OF MOBILE BANKING UNITS OF LICENSED COMMERCIAL BANKS

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
The Central Bank of Sri Lanka has issued a circular to establish guidelines for mobile banking units (MBUs) of licensed commercial banks. The goal is to strengthen the process and adopt a uniform practice among LCBs in establishing MBUs. This will empower empowerment through mobile banking.

Key Points:
- Licensed Commercial Banks (LCBs) must submit an application (BSD-MBU-01) to the Director of Bank Supervision (DBS) on a quarterly basis, 15 working days prior to the commencement of such quarter.
- The application should be submitted with a cover letter signed by the Chief Executive Officer/Chief Operating Officer or Deputy Chief Executive Officer.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

