----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T19:47:09.379579 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 08/2021: Concessions for COVID-19 Affected Businesses and Individuals

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
This circular provides concessions to businesses and individuals affected by the COVID-19 pandemic. Licensed banks are required to extend existing concessions granted under Circular No. 05 of 2021 and offer additional concessions on request. The goal is to ease the burden on borrowers who are facing financial difficulties due to the pandemic.
Key Points:
- Licensed banks must defer recovery of capital, interest, or both for existing performing credit facilities of borrowers affected by COVID-19 until 31 December 2021.
- Licensed banks may offer additional concessions to businesses and individuals affected due to the pandemic on their request, with overall benefits not less than those offered under this circular.
- Licensed banks must amalgamate amounts fallen due during previous moratorium/deferment schemes with current scheme amounts into one new loan, starting from 01 September 2021.
- Licensed banks may charge interest rates as stated in the circular, commencing from 01 September 2021, on the new loan and for agreed repayment periods.
- Concessions are available for credit facilities in both performing and non-performing categories, with specific requirements and procedures for each category.
- Licensed banks must not decline loan applications solely based on an adverse Credit Information Bureau (CRIB) record and shall develop a reporting modality to report deferment/restructuring granted under this scheme without impacting borrowers' credit scores.
- Eligible borrowers may request concessions by 21 September 2021, with licensed banks expeditiously communicating concession details and application formats via printed and/or electronic means.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

