----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T19:48:22.732257 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 10/2021: Extension of Debt Moratorium for COVID-19 Affected Businesses and Individuals in the Tourism Industry

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
This circular extends the debt moratorium for COVID-19 affected businesses and individuals in the tourism industry for another nine months. Licensed commercial banks and specialized banks are required to offer this extension to borrowers who meet certain criteria. The goal is to provide relief to those impacted by the pandemic.

Key Points:
- Licensed banks must extend the debt moratorium granted under Circular No. 08 of 2020 for another nine months, commencing October 1, 2021, and ending June 30, 2022.
- Eligible borrowers who wish to avail the moratorium must make a request to their licensed bank on or before October 15, 2021, but may be accepted if reasons for delay are acceptable.
- Licensed banks must convert capital and interest falling due during the moratorium period into a term loan and amalgamate it with previous moratorium periods.
- Licensed banks must waive off accrued and unpaid penal interest as of October 2021 on performing loans considered under this circular.
- Licensed banks must report details of moratorium availed by borrowers to the Director of Bank Supervision by the end of each month, within 15 working days.
- Licensed banks may offer alternative options such as restructuring credit facilities over a longer period or providing interest rebates to eligible borrowers who express willingness to settle existing amounts.
- Licensed banks must suspend recovery actions against non-performing facilities until June 30, 2022, and ensure that borrowers are made aware of the structure of deferment or restructuring prior to approval.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

