----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T20:52:10.737921 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 65/2025: Human Resource Policy on Remote Work

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
The Bank of Ceylon has approved a revised Human Resource Policy on Remote Work, effective from July 14th, 2025. This policy outlines guidelines and procedures for employees to work remotely, either from home or other locations outside the office.
Key Points:
- All employees are required to adhere to the Human Resource Policy on Remote Work with regard to their official duties and responsibilities.
- Employees must obtain approval from management before working remotely, and must enter into a Remote Work Agreement (RWA) prior to commencing remote work.
- Remote workers are expected to maintain confidentiality of all information concerning the businesses of the Bank, and shall be bound by the terms and conditions relating to maintaining confidentiality as outlined in the Code of Conduct, Policies, Procedures, Rules and Regulations.
- The Management shall ensure that the Remote Worker possesses necessary tools and equipment required to carry out the work from a remote work location, and the Remote Worker must use such equipment with due care.
- Remote workers are expected to be available and accessible during designated working hours, and shall report to work on allocated shift starting time or working time as agreed under the terms of the Remote Work Agreement.
- The Management reserves the sole discretion to approve or refuse an application for Remote Work Facility, and may request remote workers to participate in meetings or training conducted at the Primary Work Location of the Bank from time to time.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

