----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T20:52:26.412754 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 16/2016: Role of the Branches in Credit Card Recovery

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
This circular outlines the role of bank branches in credit card recovery for Bank of Ceylon. It emphasizes the importance of minimizing non-performing assets (NPAs) and ensuring timely payment of dues. The circular provides guidelines on procedures, eligibility, and deadlines for branch staff to follow.

Key Points:
- Branch managers must include the outstanding balance of a cardholder's Credit Card account in fresh loan proposals and restructuring/rescheduling proposals, if the account is not in the "NORM" segment.
- When processing new credit facilities or restructuring existing facilities, branches should confirm that the card account is in regular segment and carry the status "NORM". If not, action should be taken to regularize the Card Account by crediting at least the Minimum Due Amount shown in the card account/statement.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

