----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T20:52:39.679643 -----
To: employee@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular BOC-ITD-PMO-SOP-001: Project Numbering Procedure

Dear Branch Employee,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
This regulatory circular outlines a standard project classification list and procedures for allocating and changing project numbers within Bank of Ceylon's IT Project Management. The goal is to ensure consistency and accuracy in managing projects across the organization.

Key Points:
- All employees, contractors, consultants, vendors, suppliers, partners, and customers must register their projects with the PMO using the approved Project Request Form, which includes budget, benefit group, name, priority, division within Business Group, year started, project type, description, and sponsor information.
- The PMO checks the application against the project register for duplicate entries or unresolved queries, and if necessary, consults with the project manager and ITD to resolve the matter.
- A unique project number is allocated according to standard project number codes, and the project manager informs all applicable stakeholders of the project number and name.
- The PMO updates the project register, moves the project from active to closed projects, and records the date of closure upon receiving a request for project closure from the project manager.
- The PMO generates monthly reports on live and closed projects, as well as an annual running list of closed projects.
- Changes to project numbers or names require a justification and approval from the PMO, which may consult with the project sponsor, CIO, and other parties.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

