----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T20:52:53.665903 -----
To: employee@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular BOC-ITD-PMO-SOP-003: Project Risk Management Procedure

Dear Branch Employee,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
This regulatory circular outlines a project risk management procedure to help ITD project managers identify, analyze, and respond to risks throughout the project lifecycle. The goal is to ensure projects remain on track and meet their goals while minimizing potential risks.

Key Points:
- All ITD project managers must develop and implement a Project Risk Management Plan as part of the Project Management Plan.
- The Project Manager identifies, assesses, and develops mitigation plans for project risks in combination with available team members and stakeholders during each phase of the project (Initiation, Planning, Implementation, and Closure).
- The chairman of the project steering committee/sponsor approves the risks and mitigation plan, which is recorded in the project risk register.
- Risks are closed as and when assessment indicates it's possible, and new risks are recorded in regular Project Progress Reports.
- The Project Risk Register must be updated on a regular basis, and the outcome of risk review meetings leads to updating the risk register and risk paragraph of the Project Progress Report.
- The Project Management Plan and Project Risk Management Plan are approved by the Chairman of the Project Steering Committee/sponsor/other applicable party.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

