- All new documents must start with version # 1.0, and major changes will require approval from the Designated Approval Authority (DAA), while minor changes will only be reviewed by the DAA without approval.
- Document review records are maintained by the Document Controller and are accessible to authors and the ITMC.
- Documents must be published in the BOC e Learning Portal for ease of availability and accessibility, with access levels decided upon by the Information Technology Management Committee (ITMC) and CISO.
- Any change in documents must go through a Change Control process, which includes reviewing and approving changes by the ITMC before making them effective.
- Document Master List control is maintained by the Management Representative, who has overall responsibility for maintaining the master list of documents.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

