----- EMAIL 2026-07-12T20:53:49.534687 -----
To: manager@bank.lk
Subject: New Circular 32/2017: Personal Foreign Currency Account (PFCA)

Dear Compliance Manager,

A new circular has been published.

Summary:
Overview:
This Office Instructions Circular updates guidelines for Personal Foreign Currency Accounts (PFCA) to align with new regulations. It aims to facilitate the opening and maintenance of PFCA accounts while ensuring compliance with foreign exchange laws.
Key Points:
- All existing NRFC, RFC, RNNFC, NRNNFA, and FCAISPE accounts have been re-designated as Personal Foreign Currency Accounts (PFCA) with effect from 20.11.2017.
- PFCA accounts can be opened in the form of saving, current, or term deposit accounts in designated foreign currencies mentioned in Annexure I.
- Eligible persons for PFCA accounts include individuals who are Sri Lankan nationals, residents outside Sri Lanka, non-national residents in Sri Lanka, and others as specified in the circular.
- The initial deposit and minimum balance requirements are not applicable for PFCA savings and current accounts; accounts with zero balance can be opened for eligible persons.
- Interest earned on PFCA saving accounts is calculated by the system on daily balances and credited at the end of the respective month subject to a minimum interest payable of 0.10 units of the currency.
- Branches must submit a report as per Annexure VII on a monthly basis on or before the 15th day of the following month to the Department of Foreign Exchange of Central Bank of Sri Lanka.
- Fixed Deposits are opened only for those who maintain PFCA saving accounts, and deposits are accepted in designated foreign currencies mentioned in Annexure I.

Please acknowledge by 19 Jul 2026.

